      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh sensitivity study — hemolysis index convergence",
      "description": "Three mesh refinement levels (coarse ~0.30 mm, medium ~0.20 mm, fine ~0.15 mm base element size) were evaluated at the chosen settings. The fine mesh yielded a grid convergence index below 2% for normalized hemolysis index at all five operating points. Results reported at the chosen mesh size; no binding of the 0.15 mm target to the deployment configuration is recorded in this package.",
      "quantitativeResult": "GCI < 2% at fine mesh; RH range 0.61–0.89 across operating points",
      "assessmentOutcome": "Passed"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-hemolysis-threshold-sensitivity",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Power-law hemolysis threshold parameter sensitivity",
      "description": "Sensitivity of the predicted hemolysis index to the threshold shear stress parameter (range 30–80 Pa) was evaluated. At the chosen default value of 50 Pa the model matched bench NIH measurements within 12% across all five flow-speed combinations. Results are reported at the chosen settings. The deployment configuration is not required to use 50 Pa by any constraint node in this package.",
      "quantitativeResult": "NIH prediction error ≤ 12% at 50 Pa threshold; sensitivity coefficient 0.18 per 10 Pa change",
      "assessmentOutcome": "Passed"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-convergence-tolerance-check",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Iterative solver convergence tolerance verification",
      "description": "Solver residual convergence was confirmed at a target tolerance of 1e-5 for all five operating points. Comparison against a tighter tolerance of 1e-6 showed hemolysis index variation below 0.5%. Validation results are reported at the chosen convergence tolerance; no mechanism in this package enforces that the same tolerance is used in production runs.",
      "quantitativeResult": "Hemolysis index variation < 0.5% between 1e-5 and 1e-6 residual targets",
      "assessmentOutcome": "Passed"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-rh-acceptance-all-points",
