      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted using base element sizes of 0.30, 0.20, and 0.15 mm in the impeller region. Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI < 2% on the fine mesh for normalized hemolysis index at all operating points. Discretization error is acceptably characterized at the chosen mesh settings, though those settings are not formally pinned for deployment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
