      "acceptanceCriteria": "QOIs (normalized index of hemolysis, relative hemolysis index) are directly linked to the clinical endpoint and the regulatory acceptance criterion RH < 1.",
      "rationale": "The primary QOI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) aggregated to a relative hemolysis index (RH) referenced to the predicate device. RH is the accepted FDA-recognized metric for comparative hemolysis assessment. The QOIs are directly relevant to the COU decision regarding worst-case operating conditions."
    },
