      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis power-law model selection are justified with reference to literature and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on published benchmark comparisons for confined rotating flows. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model with threshold shear stress of 50 Pa was selected following a literature review of five candidate models. Sensitivity of RH to the threshold parameter was evaluated across 30–80 Pa at the chosen settings, confirming that model form uncertainty is bounded within the 12% prediction error budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
